The paper deals with the problem of learning threshold functions under the constraint of differential privacy, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). The algorithm presented in the paper involves the use of hash functions and database embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
